race.comment: Good race. BAILS (5) showed promise on debut and has upside. First outing was on heavy ground over 1420m at Grafton and boxed on well for a close-up fourth. Likely to relish the extra trip and expected to measure up. EFFIE'S JOY (7) is the main threat. Has been building to a win and just can't seem to break through. Has placed 3/3 at the trip and should be in the finish again. SHIP HAPPENS (4) was also narrowly beaten last time at Ipswich and has been knocking on the door. Must include. NIENNA (8) was safely held on heavy ground at Doomben but previous form is good for this and can bounce back.
